</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Ok, decided to play around with it again in game, and I seem to be happy with this.<br />
<br />
/hitsmode me m3 840 530 6 1 1 1 177 1<br />
/hitsmode my m5 761 503 6 1 1 1 75 0<br />
/hitsmode other m2 717 438 4 0 1 1 225 0 (might have been m3, I forget off hand)<br />
<br />
This gives you the setup I have below:<br />
<br />
<img src="http://www.lighthousepc.biz/~mwbeeler/images/example2.jpg" border="0" alt=""> <br />
<br />
Basically, the degrees of description dictate required window size.  M2 (most descriptive), M4 (least descriptive, basically just the number), and M5 (for my hits only - lists type and number).<br />
<br />
I have only tested so far with a warrior, going to play with it on Thantu a bit and see what happens when you throw spell damage into the mix and where it ends up.</p>
	
	
	
